M|Lear|Nate|
M|Lear|1. *|** append to MEMORY.md — `[date] — vt — hypothesis — result — confidence — what to tst nx`
M|Lear|2. *|** log *why* the hypothesis was wrong, not just that it failed — wrong hypotheses often reveal the right question
M|Lear|tx|3. **Experiments that produced > 15% improvement go into MEMORY.md "Growth Wins"** — proven levers that can be re-applied in new contexts
M|Lear|4. *|** treat it as an investigation, not a celebration. Random positive movement can mask underlying problems.
M|Lear|tx|5. **ICE scores are estimates, not facts.** If an ICE-scored experiment consistently under/over-performs the score, recalibrate the scoring md.
